  <title>GLib.atomic_int_add</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function atomic_int_add(atomic: Number(gint), val: Number(gint)): Number(gint) {
    // Gjs wrapper for g_atomic_int_add()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Atomically adds <code>val</code> to the value of <code>atomic</code>.</p>  <p>Think of this operation as an atomic version of
`{ tmp = *atomic; *atomic += val; return tmp; }`.</p>  <p>This call acts as a full compiler and hardware memory barrier.</p>  <p>Before version 2.30, this function did not return a value
(but <link xref="GLib.atomic_int_exchange_and_add"/> did, and had the same meaning).</p>
  <p>Since 2.4</p>
